Fortis is looking for a Technical Business Analyst to join our engineering team to analyze, document, and work with our software development team to build API connectors to the various data sources.

The applicant will be working with our product, engineering, and analyst teams to deliver access to big data in the transportation industry.

Key Responsibilities:
Have an in-depth understanding of transportation data sources.
Work with analysts to use data to identify the best APIs to integrate with for each source.
Document detailed user stories and business requirements so that developers have sufficient information to code each API.
Act as liaison with analysts on data challenges and help troubleshoot technical solutions.
Help define the vision for a product, identify dead ends and routes with untapped potential.
Work with both the account teams at the agencies as well as the clients.
Work with the engineering team to troubleshoot high-level technical issues within the platform.
Work with the Product Marketing/Product Analysts to scale an onboarding.

Required Skills:
– 2+ years writing detailed business requirements;
– 2+ years writing user stories and documenting acceptance criteria;
– 3+ years working in an Agile methodology;
– Experience working with a variety of APIs and understanding data APIs;
– Experience translating business requirements into technical requirements;
– Experience working with development teams;
– Intellectual curiosity and drive, self-starters will thrive in this position;
– Passion for Technology: Excitement for new technology, bleeding edge applications, and a positive attitude towards solving real-world challenges.

Education & Experience:
BA in Computer Information Systems or Bachelors in Business Administration.

