Conduct and Control BA – New York, New York
About the team:
Capco is looking for a Consultant / Senior Consultant to join our expanding Finance, Risk and Compliance and Capital Markets practices to provide business analysis and subject matter expertise to our clients. This person will have the ability to support clients in regulatory remediations and improving control and surveillance around conduct within our clients’ Capital Markets functions
About the Job:
The candidate will support regulatory remediation programs for our clients, providing subject matter expertise, business analysis and project management skills to improve internal conduct and controls. Specifically, this candidate will support improving client’s Conduct Frameworks around sales and trading practices.
What You’ll Get to Do:
Key Activities
Collate documents, data and associated MI to support an assessment of the design effectiveness and adequacy of the controls in place to mitigate/ manage the identified risks. The assessment should include a review to ensure adherence with firm policies in place;
Work with traders and infrastructure staff to design a set of controls as part of a Conduct Framework to address gaps identified during the assessment process;
Work with Sales and Trading stakeholders and the appropriate infrastructure teams, including Technology, to define an implementation plan and determine how the implementation can be optimized and/ or phased to put effective controls in place efficiently. Identify appropriate technology solutions to enhance control and determine where interim tactical solutions are required;
Remediate the enhancement actions/conduct action plans specific to Supervision and Policy & Procedure change as the Action Delivery Lead
Work with client stakeholders to support the administration and review of new and/or changes to Policy and Procedures impacting the Front Office including tracking the implementation effectiveness.
Draft clear and concise procedures which provide effective guidance for sales and trading and design training to communicate and reinforce procedure change.
Ensure all assessment, design and implementation activities engage an appropriate and complete set of stakeholders across relevant product groups and supporting infrastructure functions and are performed within the defined scope of the programme and support its objectives;
Work with client stakeholders to ensure adequate delivery plans are defined and agreed with the relevant stakeholders, ensuring planning is performed at the appropriate level such that all stakeholders involved in the production of deliverables are engaged and clearly understand how their contribution meets the objectives and benefits targeted by the wider programme;
Actively identify, assess and manage risks and issues that arise in defining a control framework for conflicts, ensuring they are monitored and managed appropriately to minimise impact on delivery, escalating to senior stakeholders, as needed
What You’ll Bring with You:
Business Analyst/PM experience (at least 5 years relevant experience in IB Front Office environment);
Evidence of a successful track record delivering change in an IB Front Office environment;
Has experience of delivering non-technology driven Excellent analytical skills;
Excellent written skills and experience of drafting policies and procedures;
Good communication skills and ability to operate at multiple levels;
Has experience of managing senior stakeholders and ability to build strong relationships;
Collaborative style with ability to quickly build trust and credibility;
Good understanding of project management and business analysis best practices, methodologies and the project lifecycle;
IB Sales & Trading experience including an understanding of conflicts of interest, trading controls, control frameworks, risk management & regulatory demands;
Why Capco?
You will join a company that supports and encourages an entrepreneurial outlook and independent thinking. Capco is not about organizational charts and layers – we operate with little hierarchy because we want all employees to feel that Capco is their firm.

We offer highly competitive benefits, including medical, dental and vision insurance, a 401(k) plan, tuition reimbursement, and a work culture focused on innovation and creation of lasting value for our clients and employees.

Ready to take the Next Step
If this sounds like you, we would love to hear from you. This is an opportunity to make a difference and contribute to a highly successful company with a significant growth trajectory.

